                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/899: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 5, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Your 2, January 3, 4 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Draft of proposed note is approved.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Department’s records do not clearly indicate whether the particular
                        taxes involved in this case are paid by virtue of a private <pb facs="0936"
                            n="792" xml:id="pg_792"/> tax agreement or are paid by the public
                        generally. The Department assumes that consular officers are careful to
                        avoid basing their representations on the stipulations of private agreements
                        for the payment of extra treaty taxes.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
